# temflowral — project overview

Visual workflow engine: users draw a graph in React Flow (frontend), the backend
translates it into a Temporal workflow and runs it. Go backend, Next.js/TypeScript
frontend, Temporal for durable execution.

## Contract-first workflow — this is the most important thing to know

`api/openapi.yaml` is the source of truth for the HTTP API. It is authored and
updated BEFORE backend handlers or frontend calls are written, not after.

- Backend generates server interfaces/types from the spec (oapi-codegen or
  equivalent). Do not write request/response structs by hand that duplicate
  what codegen should produce.
- Frontend generates a typed client from the spec (openapi-typescript / orval).
  Do not hand-write fetch calls with inline types for endpoints that exist in
  the spec.
- If a feature needs an API change, edit `openapi.yaml` first, regenerate both
  sides, then implement. Never let backend and frontend drift by hand-editing
  around a stale contract.
- Anything under a generated-code directory (look for a
  "Code generated by ... DO NOT EDIT" header) should be regenerated, not
  hand-edited.

## Team split

- Backend + frontend integration: primary contributor.
- Automated testing (Playwright): second contributor, builds against a Prism
  mock server generated from `openapi.yaml`, not against the live backend.

## Where things live

- `api/openapi.yaml` — the contract.
- `backend/` — Go module `github.com/madmmas/temflowral/backend`.
- `frontend/` — Next.js app.
- `ISSUES.md` — current backlog and build order.
- `DEVLOG.md` — running progress log. Add an entry per work session; don't skip it.

## General guidance

- This is an early-stage project (day 0/1 as of kickoff). Expect a lot of
  scaffolding work before real logic. Don't over-engineer abstractions for
  node types that don't exist yet — the first real node type is the HTTP
  activity node; SECURITY.md already flags it as the main attack surface
  (SSRF, template injection in config, arbitrary outbound requests), so build
  validation alongside it, not after.
- Prefer editing `ISSUES.md` and `DEVLOG.md` to reflect real decisions over
  keeping the plan only in chat history.
